<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7709&amp;p=77616#p77616"><![CDATA[
Drag, using a small capacitor from Vcc to Ground is a commonly used method of "debouncing" the supply voltage for an IC. The few electronics books I have read suggest doing this.<br /><br />Keep in mind that a capacitor, especially one of low capacitance, does not create a shunt. I do not exactly understand how it "debounces" the supply voltage, but I know it does not short the circuit.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3706">qbradq</a> — Wed May 04, 2011 11:26 am</p><hr />
